Application Overview
RevWorkforce is a full-stack monolithic Human Resource Management (HRM) web application designed to streamline employee management, leave tracking, and performance review processes. The system supports three user roles: Employees, Managers, and Admins, each with specific functionalities accessible through an intuitive web interface. The application features responsive design, role-based dashboards, and automated notifications.

Core Functional Requirements
As an Employee, I should be able to:
Authentication & Profile
1.	Login to my account using employee ID/email and password
2.	View my dashboard with key information (leave balance, pending leaves)
3.	Edit basic profile information (phone number, address, emergency contact)
4.	View my complete profile details
5.	View my reporting manager details
Leave Management Module
6.	View available leave balance by type (Casual Leave, Sick Leave, Paid Leave)
7.	Apply for leave with start date, end date, leave type, and reason
8.	View all applied leaves with status (Pending/Approved/Rejected)
9.	Cancel pending leave applications
10.	View company holiday calendar
11.	Receive in-app notifications when leave is approved or rejected
Performance Management Module
12.	Create performance review document with key deliverables, accomplishments, areas of improvement, and self-assessment rating
13.	Submit performance review to manager
14.	View submitted performance reviews with status
15.	Set goals for the year with goal description, deadline, and priority (High/Medium/Low)
16.	View all my goals with status
17.	Update goal progress
18.	View manager's feedback on performance review
19.	Receive notifications when manager provides feedback
Additional Features
20.	View company announcements
21.	Access employee directory with search functionality

As a Manager, I should be able to:
Note: All managers are employees, so they have access to all employee features plus the following:
Leave Management Module
1.	View list of direct reportees (employees reporting to me)
2.	View leave applications from team members
3.	Approve leave requests with optional comments
4.	Reject leave requests with mandatory comments
5.	View team leave calendar showing team members' leaves
6.	View leave balance of team members
7.	Receive in-app notifications when team member applies for leave
Performance Management Module
8.	View performance reviews submitted by direct reportees
9.	Provide detailed feedback on employee performance reviews
10.	Rate employee performance using rating scale (1-5)
11.	Submit performance review feedback
12.	Review employee goals and provide comments
13.	View team member goal progress
14.	Receive notifications when employee submits performance review
Team Management
15.	View team structure
16.	Access team member profiles

As an Admin, I should be able to:
Employee Management
1.	Add new employees with complete details (personal information, employee ID, department, designation, joining date, manager assignment, salary)
2.	Update employee information
3.	View all employee details with search and filters
4.	Deactivate employee accounts
5.	Reactivate employee accounts
6.	Assign reporting manager to employees
7.	Change reporting managers
8.	Search employees by name, employee ID, department, or designation
Leave Management
9.	Configure leave types (Casual Leave, Sick Leave, Paid Leave)
10.	Assign leave quotas to employees by leave type
11.	Adjust leave balances manually with reason
12.	View all employee leave information
13.	Generate leave reports (department-wise, employee-wise)
14.	Set and manage company holiday calendar
15.	Add/edit/delete company holidays
System Configuration
16.	Manage departments (add, edit, delete, view)
17.	Manage designations/job titles (add, edit, delete, view)
18.	Create and manage company announcements
19.	View system activity logs
Reporting
20.	View dashboard with key HR metrics (total employees, leave statistics)
21.	Generate employee reports
22.	Generate leave utilization reports

Standard Functional Scope
•	Authentication & Security
•	Notification System
•	User Interface & Experience
•	Data Management
Definition of Done
1.	Working Web Application Demonstration
2.	Code Repository Submission with:
a)	ERD (Entity Relationship Diagram) 
b)	Application Architecture Diagram 
c)	README.md 
d)	Testing Artifacts
